value.name: Montreal | Location, History, Population, Languages, Climate, & Facts
value.snippet: Montreal, French Montréal, city, Quebec province, southeastern Canada. Montreal is the second most-populous city in Canada and the principal metropolis of the province of Quebec. The city of Montreal occupies about three-fourths of Montreal Island (Île de Montréal), the largest of the 234 islands of the Hochelaga Archipelago, one of three archipelagoes near the confluence of the Ottawa and St. Lawrence rivers.

value.name: What to do | Tourisme Montréal
value.snippet: What to do. Montréal is a big, busy, exhilarating city, with so much to see and do. There’ll be plenty of long walks and bike rides, picnics at the park, street art hunts and time to discover the city’s many treasures. We invite you to explore the many “moments” you can experience in the city.

value.name: Montréal – Wikipedia
value.snippet: Montréal ligger sørvest i Québec, omtrent 200 km sørvest for provinsens hovedstad Québec by og 150 km øst for Ottawa, Canadas hovedstad. Byen ligger på den fluviale øya Île de Montréal («Montréal-øya») ved samløpet av elvene Ottawa og St. Lawrence.
